DPRK Stand to Contribute to Peace and Security in Asia Clarified 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tehran, November 15 (KCNA) -- The parliamentarians representing the voices of the Asian people, aware of the sense of responsibility as the master of the continent, should thoroughly reject the moves of the hegemonic forces to stamp out the history, culture and tradition of Asia, place the common denominators above their differences and demonstrate the united strength of the region in one voice in the international arena under the slogan of solidarity, peace and justice of Asia. Choe Thae Bok, chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, who is leading the delegation of the DPRK to the 7th Assembly of the Association of Asian Parliaments for Peace held in Iran, declared this in a speech at its plenary meeting on Nov. 13.
 He said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The struggle of the Korean people to achieve the reunification and denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula is now facing a grave challenge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush administration, in particular, openly listed the DPRK as part of an "axis of evil" and a target of preemptive nuclear attack and has since escalated the threat and pressure upon the DPRK such as staging nuclear war exercises and imposing financial sanctions against it, bringing to light an attempt to bring down its social system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the extremely tense situation where the supreme interests and security of the DPRK were seriously threatened it successfully conducted on Oct. 9 an underground nuclear test under secure conditions as an exercise of its sovereign right to self-defence to cope with the U.S. nuclear threat, sanctions and pressure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will surely force the Bush administration to own its historic responsibility for having torpedoed the process of denuclearizing the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It remains unchanged in its stand to peacefully realize the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula through dialogue and negotiation though it was compelled to conduct the nuclear test by the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the DPRK has already clarified, its nuclear weapons are war deterrent for self-defence to cope with the U.S. nuclear threat and sanctions which have reached an extreme phase and it will feel no need to keep even a single nuke if the U.S. ceases its nuclear threat and sanctions against the DPRK in a verifiable and trustworthy manner.
 Availing ourselves of this opportunity, we express thanks to the Asian people who sent support and solidarity to our people in their struggle for the peace, reunification and denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and believe that the invariable will of the DPRK for the denuclearization and the independent option of its people to protect the supreme interests of the state will receive well-deserved respect. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will as always unite close with the Asian people and make a positive contribution to peace, security, independent development and prosperity of Asia.

Japanese Imperialists' Fabrication of "Ulsa Five-point Treaty" under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 17 (KCNA) -- The Secretariat of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland made public information bulletin No. 926 on Thursday, 101 years since the Japanese imperialists fabricated the "Ulsa (1905) Five-Point Treaty" to establish colonial domination over Korea.
 It said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the strength of the "Ulsa Five-Point Treaty" the Japanese imperialists occupied the whole of Korea and turned it into their colony. Since then the Korean nation had suffered unbearable humiliation, maltreatment, cruel sacrifices and misfortune, the distress and tragedy as a ruined nation for more than 40 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the occupation of Korea the Japanese imperialists unhesitatingly committed the most hideous crimes against humanity in history. They massacred at least one million innocent Koreans, forcibly drafted more than 8.4 million Koreans to impose slave labor upon them and forced more than 200,000 Korean women into "sexual slavery" for the Japanese aggressor army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They severely destroyed and looted precious cultural treasures and natural resources of Korea and made no scruple of depriving the Koreans of their written and spoken languages and their own names in a bid to enslave them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their fabrication of the "Ulsa Five-Point Treaty" and colonial domination over Korea were the most brigandish and hideous state-sponsored crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is obliged to apologize and compensate for the crimes committed against the Koreans in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, Japan has worked hard to beautify and justify the hideous state-sponsored crimes committed in the past, instead of reflecting on them and making an apology for them before the Koreans and other peoples of the world. It is keen to stage a comeback to Korea, distorting history and eyeing even its inviolable territory including Tok Islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is more desperately pursuing its hostile policy towards the DPRK, zealously joining the U.S. in its sanctions and pressure upon it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Koreans including the south Koreans should more dynamically turn out in a more dynamic anti-Japanese struggle to force Japan to redeem all the crimes committed by the Japanese imperialists against the Korean nation and frustrate the Japanese reactionaries' moves for reinvasion so that they may not suffer the same disgrace and ordeals as the Koreans did in the past.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Higher Display of Korean Nation-first Spirit 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 17 (KCNA) -- The viewpoint of attaching importance to the nation and the nation-first spirit is a genuine patriotic viewpoint promoting the nation's independent shaping of its destiny, says Rodong Sinmun in an article Friday.
 Noting that to adhere to the viewpoint and stand of attaching importance to the nation and the nation-first spirit is a very important way of speeding up the patriotic movement for independent reunification, the author of the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the members of the nation fail to maintain the viewpoint and morale of attaching importance to the nation and the nation-first spirit, they cannot withstand the challenges of outside aggression forces nor can they shape the destiny of the nation independently. In the present times it stands out with greater urgency to struggle with this steadfast ideological standpoint and morale. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation is now living in the June 15 era of reunification. The progress of the era would have been unthinkable without these viewpoint and morale. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present times have witnessed evermore desperate moves of the outside forces in their interference in the internal affairs of the Korean nation intended to block its cause of independent reunification and undermine the inter-Korean relations and their moves to provoke a war against the DPRK. No force on earth will or can save the Korean nation from the danger of war. Destructive would be the consequences to be entailed by the stance of attaching importance to outside forces and dependence on them under this situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Only when the Koreans cherish the viewpoint of attaching importance to the nation and the nation-first spirit and decisively oppose flunkeyism and dependence on outside forces, establishing the spirit of fighting with the joint efforts of the Korean nation itself, can they triumphantly push forward the cause of independent reunification, frustrating the interference of outside forces and their moves for aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Deeply cherishing the spirit of attaching importance to the nation and the nation-first spirit, the Korean nation will vigorously hew the path of the cause of independent reunification under the uplifted banner of "By our nation itself".

Solidarity Meeting for DPRK Held in Switzerland 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 17 (KCNA) -- A meeting for solidarity with the DPRK took place in Basel, Switzerland, on Nov. 11 under the sponsorship of the Swiss Committee for Supporting the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea.
 The chairman of the committee in his speech at the meeting said that the Korean people have made great achievements under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, adding that the DPRK made a breakthrough towards the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has exerted strenuous efforts for the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula for years and steadily bolstered its national defense capability for protecting the sovereignty of the country from the U.S. moves for a new war and nuclear threat, he noted, calling upon the world people to stage a more dynamic movement for supporting the Korean people in their just struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting.

Footballers Feted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 17 (KCNA) -- The Cabinet of the DPRK Thursday arranged a banquet welcoming home the footballers who took the title of the AFC Under-19 Soccer Championship.
 Present at the banquet together with the young footballers were Kwak Pom Gi, vice-premier of the Cabinet, Choe Nam Gyun, minister of Food Procurement and Administration who is chairman of the DPRK Football Association, Mun Jae Dok, chairman of the DPRK Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission, Pang Chol Gap, chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee, and sports officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kwak Pom Gi in his speech said the young footballers gave great strength and courage to the army and people of the DPRK in dynamically pushing forward the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation by overwhelming powerful Asian teams and winning the champion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He urged the young footballers to achieve brilliant success at the forthcoming FIFA U-20 World Cup by undergoing intensive training in the revolutionary soldier spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speaking in reply, Kim Kum Il, captain of the team, said the young footballers would present a report of victory and glory to Kim Jong Il by further completing the Korean-style tactics through the training for the FIFA U-20 World Cup.

Freedom of Meetings and Demos Demanded in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 17 (KCNA) -- The "Joint Conference for Ensuring Freedom of Unfettered and Peaceful Meetings and Demos" consisting of at least 90 civic and public organizations of south Korea reportedly held a press conference in front of the Seoul Metropolitan Police Office on Nov. 13 to demand the security authorities ensure the freedom of meetings and demos.
 The press conference was called in connection with the fact that the police office recently put forward the so-called "guidelines for strengthening countermeasure at the site of a meeting and a demo" banning meetings in the centre of the city and declared that "if a press conference or a cultural event is judged as an illegal meeting, it will strengthen roundup of participants on the spot." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the press conference asserted that the police office should ensure the freedom of meetings and demos of civic and public organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release was read out there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It noted that in the past the UN organization recommended south Korea to amend articles of the "law on meetings and demos" which bans meetings. It urged the police office to repeal all the measures going against the freedom of meetings and demos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The authorities should amend the evil laws so that the freedom of meetings and demos may be ensured, the release said, stressing that the organizations would struggle to check the action of the police office.

S. Korean Warmongers' Arms Buildup Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 17 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Friday carries a signed commentary denouncing the south Korean warmongers' arms buildup.
 The south Korean warlike forces are recently spurring on developing ultra-modern war equipment aiming at the DPRK, the commentary says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is an open provocation and challenge to the DPRK and an anti-national crime of bringing military confrontation and war between the north and the south in cooperation with the U.S. imperialists' moves for a war against the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean bellicose forces' frenzy development of ultra-modern war equipment against fellow countrymen, synchronizing with the U.S. imperialists' racket of sanctions and pressure on the DPRK, is a clear revelation of their pro-U.S. sycophantic traitorous nature of betraying the nation as henchmen of the outside forces' moves for an aggressive war and harassing the peace of the country and blocking the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is not only this time that their criminal action was brought to light. In recent days alone, they amended and supplemented the already-prepared provocative war operation plans against the DPRK, making much ado about someone's "threat" in conspiracy with the U.S. imperialists. They are now busy introducing latest precision striking weapons including F-15K, Aegis destroyer and air-to-ground guided missiles ahead of the schedule. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their action cannot be justified by anything. The Korean nation will never pardon the pro-U.S. warmongers hurting national dignity and interests.

Kimchi-making for Winter at Its Height
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 17 (KCNA) -- The season of making Kimchi for the winter has come in Korea.
 Kimchi, a world-famous foodstuff, is the pride of the Korean women. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the ardent wish of the housewives to prepare tasty Kimchi. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recently, hundreds of women phone the Phyongchon Kimchi Factory every day regarding technical issues raised in making winter Kimchi. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The topic among women is how to prepare tasty Kimchi. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The TVs and the radios introduce the methods of making various kinds of winter Kimchi as well as the powder of Kimchi lactic acid bacilli, fluid for culturing Kimchi lactic acid bacilli, Kimchi fluorine preservative and others which keep the inherent taste of Kimchi and preserve it for months. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Foodstuff shops and public service facilities are crowded with women to purchase condiments needed for Kimchi. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Sun Hui, 65, in Ryonhwa-dong No. 1 of Central District, Pyongyang said KCNA that she would make very tasty Kimchi this time with 20 odd condiments. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Making winter Kimchi, she added, shows the cookery of each housewife. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has been a living custom in every November that families, relatives, neighbors and workshop members bring their Kimchi and condiments to taste each other. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the efforts of the Korean women who value national food, the Korean Kimchi with a long history is developing with unique taste.

Talented Korean Painting Creators
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 17 (KCNA) -- The Korean Paintings "Reunification Rainbow" and "Masque Dance in Pongsan" created in the Mansudae Art Studio of the DPRK were awarded the gold prizes, top prize, in the recent 9th Beijing International Art Exhibition.
 They were drawn by Kim Song Min and Kim Sung Hui. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Labor Hero and People's Artist Kim Song Min laureate with Kim Il Sung Prize is a competent artist who has developed the creation of figure painting with the Korean painting technique in the nation's artistic world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has produced more than 1,000 pieces of fine-art for over three decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them, tens of his works were registered as national treasures and over ten works were awarded gold medals in various international fine-art exhibitions and fairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, "Sun of All People" created by him in Juche 83 (1994) was highly appreciated as a masterpiece of the times for its high degree of ideological and artistic value. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People's Artist Kim Sung Hui laureate with Kim Il Sung Prize is a famous woman artist in the country. She produced a lot of Korean paintings worthy of national treasure during her 40-odd-year creative career. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is characteristic in her works is the application of the single-stroke method of the Korean painting. In the aspect of content, she drew many figure, landscape and genre paintings reflecting desire of fellow-countrymen for the national reunification and superiority of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are "Grudge of Kwangju", "Reunification Dance", "Chilsong Gate in Spring".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She was repatriated to the socialist motherland from Japan in September 1959. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though she is far over sixty, she is still working hard full of vigor.

Japanese Reactionaries' Escalated Suppression of Chongryon Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 17 (KCNA) -- The Japanese reactionaries have escalated the suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) while crying for "intensified sanctions" against the DPRK over its measure of bolstering the war deterrent for self-defense.
 Describing this as a token of the uneasiness of criminals, a Minju Joson analyst Friday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan, truth to tell, has a past full of crimes which it committed during its harsh colonial rule over Korea while occupying it for more than 40 years. These hideous state-sponsored crimes started with the fabrication of the "Ulsa (1905) Five-Point Treaty." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. divided the Korean nation after the Second World War by taking advantage of the Japanese imperialists' enforcement of the colonial rule based on the treaty for scores of years. Explicitly speaking, but for the Japanese imperialists' occupation of Korea and enforcement of the colonial rule over it, the U.S. would not have made its way into south Korea after Korea's liberation under the pretext of disarming the Imperial Japanese Army and the Korean nation would not have undergone the tragic division for more than six decades. The misfortunes and pains the Korean nation has suffered for more than a century trace their origin to Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is preposterous for Japan to raise a hue and cry over "a threat to security," taking issue with the DPRK over its measure of bolstering the war deterrent for self-defense. This reveals its grievances at having become unable to realize its reinvasion scheme due to the DPRK's increased war deterrent.
